[2] South Carolina: canine (fox), human exposure
Date: Fri 30 Sep 2016 7:57 PM CEDT
Source: Live 5 News, WIS, SC Department of Health and Environmental Control (DHEC) report [edited]
http://www.live5news.com/story/33288882/person-treated-for-rabies-after-exposure-to-richland-co-fox


A person is being treated for possible rabies exposure after coming into contact with a fox that tested positive for the disease in Richland County [South Carolina]. The South Carolina Department of Health and Environmental Control (DHEC) reports that the victim was bitten by the fox in the Arcadia Lakes neighborhood on 26 Sep 2016. The fox was submitted to the DHEC lab for testing and rabies was confirmed.

This is the 3rd animal in Richland County to test positive for rabies in 2016. There have been 78 confirmed cases of animal rabies statewide this year [2016]. In 2015, 11 of the 130 rabies cases in South Carolina were in Richland County.

