[The state of Missouri can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4547976,55935. Cass County in west central Missouri can be seen on the map at http://geology.com/county-map/missouri-county-map.gif. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ

None of the articles above indicate whether the community is conducting a specific anti-rabies vaccination drive to vaccinate animals and a campaign to educate people on the signs of rabies as well as the importance of vaccinating their pets.

While there is post exposure prophylaxis (PEP) for people there is no such treatment for a pet that is not vaccinated but has been exposed to a rabid animal. Unvaccinated pets that are exposed to a rabid animal are euthanized. What heartbreak to the family or person who could have saved their pet by having it vaccinated.

People should be aware that post exposure prophylaxis is expensive. Some places charge in the thousands of dollars for the series. There are a variety of rules for people with known bites versus those with possible exposure http://www.cdc.gov/rabies/exposure/index.html.

Rabies is a serious disease and should not be taken lightly in animals or people. - Mod.TG]
